\f0\b\fs64 \cf2 Joshua 
\b0\fs24 \cf3 \

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 1
\b0\fs26 \cf3 After the death of Moses the servant of the LORD, it came to pass that the LORD spoke to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses' assistant, saying: 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 "Moses My servant is dead. Now therefore, arise, go over this Jordan, you and all this people, to the land which I am giving to them--the children of Israel. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given you, as I said to Moses. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 From the wilderness and this Lebanon as far as the great river, the River Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites, and to the Great Sea toward the going down of the sun, shall be your territory. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 No man shall be able to stand before you all the days of your life; as I was with Moses, so I will be with you. I will not leave you nor forsake you. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Be strong and of good courage, for to this people you shall divide as an inheritance the land which I swore to their fathers to give them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Only be strong and very courageous, that you may observe to do according to all the law which Moses My servant commanded you; do not turn from it to the right hand or to the left, that you may prosper wherever you go. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall meditate in it day and night, that you may observe to do according to all that is written in it. For then you will make your way prosperous, and then you will have good success. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Have I not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage; do not be afraid, nor be dismayed, for the LORD your God is with you wherever you go." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 "Pass through the camp and command the people, saying, "Prepare provisions for yourselves, for within three days you will cross over this Jordan, to go in to possess the land which the LORD your God is giving you to possess."' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh Joshua spoke, saying, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 "Remember the word which Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, saying, "The LORD your God is giving you rest and is giving you this land.' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in the land which Moses gave you on this side of the Jordan. But you shall pass before your brethren armed, all your mighty men of valor, and help them, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 until the LORD has given your brethren rest, as He gave you, and they also have taken possession of the land which the LORD your God is giving them. Then you shall return to the land of your possession and enjoy it, which Moses the LORD's servant gave you on this side of the Jordan toward the sunrise." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So they answered Joshua, saying, "All that you command us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Just as we heeded Moses in all things, so we will heed you. Only the LORD your God be with you, as He was with Moses. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Whoever rebels against your command and does not heed your words, in all that you command him, shall be put to death. Only be strong and of good courage." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 2
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now Joshua the son of Nun sent out two men from Acacia Grove to spy secretly, saying, "Go, view the land, especially Jericho." So they went, and came to the house 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 of a harlot named Rahab, and lodged there. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it was told the king of Jericho, saying, "Behold, men have come here tonight from the children of Israel to search out the country." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the king of Jericho sent to Rahab, saying, "Bring out the men who have come to you, who have entered your house, for they have come to search out all the country." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the woman took the two men and hid them. So she said, "Yes, the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it happened as the gate was being shut, when it was dark, that the men went out. Where the men went I do not know; pursue them quickly, for you may overtake them." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 (But she had brought them up to the roof and hidden them with the stalks of flax, which she had laid in order on the roof.) 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the men pursued them by the road to the Jordan, to the fords. And as soon as those who pursued them had gone out, they shut the gate. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now before they lay down, she came up to them on the roof, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and said to the men: "I know that the LORD has given you the land, that the terror of you has fallen on us, and that all the inhabitants of the land are fainthearted because of you. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 For we have heard how the LORD dried up the water of the Red Sea for you when you came out of Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of the Amorites who were on the other side of the Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom you utterly destroyed. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And as soon as we heard these things, our hearts melted; neither did there remain any more courage in anyone because of you, for the LORD your God, He is God in heaven above and on earth beneath. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now therefore, I beg you, swear to me by the LORD, since I have shown you kindness, that you also will show kindness to my father's house, and give me a true token, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and spare my father, my mother, my brothers, my sisters, and all that they have, and deliver our lives from death." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the men answered her, "Our lives for yours, if none of you tell this business of ours. And it shall be, when the LORD has given us the land, that we will deal kindly and truly with you." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house was on the city wall; she dwelt on the wall. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And she said to them, "Get to the mountain, lest the pursuers meet you. Hide there three days, until the pursuers have returned. Afterward you may go your way." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the men said to her: "We will be blameless of this oath of yours which you have made us swear, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 unless, when we come into the land, you bind this line of scarlet cord in the window through which you let us down, and unless you bring your father, your mother, your brothers, and all your father's household to your own home. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it shall be that whoever goes outside the doors of your house into the street, his blood shall be on his own head, and we will be guiltless. And whoever is with you in the house, his blood shall be on our head if a hand is laid on him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And if you tell this business of ours, then we will be free from your oath which you made us swear." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then she said, "According to your words, so be it." And she sent them away, and they departed. And she bound the scarlet cord in the window. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 They departed and went to the mountain, and stayed there three days until the pursuers returned. The pursuers sought them all along the way, but did not find them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the two men returned, descended from the mountain, and crossed over; and they came to Joshua the son of Nun, and told him all that had befallen them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And they said to Joshua, "Truly the LORD has delivered all the land into our hands, for indeed all the inhabitants of the country are fainthearted because of us." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 3
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Then Joshua rose early in the morning; and they set out from Acacia Grove and came to the Jordan, he and all the children of Israel, and lodged there before they 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 crossed over. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it was, after three days, that the officers went through the camp; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and they commanded the people, saying, "When you see the ark of the covenant of the LORD your God, and the priests, the Levites, bearing it, then you shall set out from your place and go after it. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Yet there shall be a space between you and it, about two thousand cubits by measure. Do not come near it, that you may know the way by which you must go, for you have not passed this way before." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Joshua said to the people, "Sanctify yourselves, for tomorrow the LORD will do wonders among you." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Joshua spoke to the priests, saying, "Take up the ark of the covenant and cross over before the people." So they took up the ark of the covenant and went before the people. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD said to Joshua, "This day I will begin to exalt you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that, as I was with Moses, so I will be with you. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 You shall command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, saying, "When you have come to the edge of the water of the Jordan, you shall stand in the Jordan."' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Joshua said to the children of Israel, "Come here, and hear the words of the LORD your God." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Joshua said, "By this you shall know that the living God is among you, and that He will without fail drive out from before you the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Hivites and the Perizzites and the Girgashites and the Amorites and the Jebusites: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Behold, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is crossing over before you into the Jordan. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now therefore, take for yourselves twelve men from the tribes of Israel, one man from every tribe. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it shall come to pass, as soon as the soles of the feet of the priests who bear the ark of the LORD, the Lord of all the earth, shall rest in the waters of the Jordan, that the waters of the Jordan shall be cut off, the waters that come down from upstream, and they shall stand as a heap." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it was, when the people set out from their camp to cross over the Jordan, with the priests bearing the ark of the covenant before the people, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and as those who bore the ark came to the Jordan, and the feet of the priests who bore the ark dipped in the edge of the water (for the Jordan overflows all its banks during the whole time of harvest), 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 that the waters which came down from upstream stood still, and rose in a heap very far away at Adam, the city that is beside Zaretan. So the waters that went down into the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, failed, and were cut off; and the people crossed over opposite Jericho. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the LORD stood firm on dry ground in the midst of the Jordan; and all Israel crossed over on dry ground, until all the people had crossed completely over the Jordan. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 4
\b0\fs26 \cf3 And it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed over the Jordan, that the LORD spoke to Joshua, saying: 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 "Take for yourselves twelve men from the people, one man from every tribe, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and command them, saying, "Take for yourselves twelve stones from here, out of the midst of the Jordan, from the place where the priests' feet stood firm. You shall carry them over with you and leave them in the lodging place where you lodge tonight."' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Joshua called the twelve men whom he had appointed from the children of Israel, one man from every tribe; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and Joshua said to them: "Cross over before the ark of the LORD your God into the midst of the Jordan, and each one of you take up a stone on his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 that this may be a sign among you when your children ask in time to come, saying, "What do these stones mean to you?' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then you shall answer them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off before the ark of the covenant of the LORD; when it crossed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. And these stones shall be for a memorial to the children of Israel forever." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the children of Israel did so, just as Joshua commanded, and took up twelve stones from the midst of the Jordan, as the LORD had spoken to Joshua, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel, and carried them over with them to the place where they lodged, and laid them down there. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Joshua set up twelve stones in the midst of the Jordan, in the place where the feet of the priests who bore the ark of the covenant stood; and they are there to this day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the priests who bore the ark stood in the midst of the Jordan until everything was finished that the LORD had commanded Joshua to speak to the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua; and the people hurried and crossed over. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed over, that the ark of the LORD and the priests crossed over in the presence of the people. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the men of Reuben, the men of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh crossed over armed before the children of Israel, as Moses had spoken to them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 About forty thousand prepared for war crossed over before the LORD for battle, to the plains of Jericho. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 On that day the LORD exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and they feared him, as they had feared Moses, all the days of his life. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD spoke to Joshua, saying,\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 "Command the priests who bear the ark of the Testimony to come up from the 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 Jordan." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Joshua therefore commanded the priests, saying, "Come up from the Jordan." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it came to pass, when the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the LORD had come from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests' feet touched the dry land, that the waters of the Jordan returned to their place and overflowed all its banks as before. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now the people came up from the Jordan on the tenth day of the first month, and they camped in Gilgal on the east border of Jericho. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And those twelve stones which they took out of the Jordan, Joshua set up in Gilgal. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he spoke to the children of Israel, saying: "When your children ask their 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 fathers in time to come, saying, "What are these stones?' 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 then you shall let your children know, saying, "Israel crossed over this Jordan on dry land'; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 for the LORD your God dried up the waters of the Jordan before you until you had crossed over, as the LORD your God did to the Red Sea, which He dried up before us until we had crossed over, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 that all the peoples of the earth may know the hand of the LORD, that it is mighty, that you may fear the LORD your God forever." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 5
\b0\fs26 \cf3 So it was, when all the kings of the Amorites who were on the west side of the Jordan, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the sea, heard that the 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 LORD had dried up the waters of the Jordan from before the children of Israel until we had crossed over, that their heart melted; and there was no spirit in them any longer because of the children of Israel. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 At that time the LORD said to Joshua, "Make flint knives for yourself, and circumcise the sons of Israel again the second time." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Joshua made flint knives for himself, and circumcised the sons of Israel at the hill of the foreskins. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And this is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: All the people who came out of Egypt who were males, all the men of war, had died in the wilderness on the way, after they had come out of Egypt. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 For all the people who came out had been circumcised, but all the people born in the wilderness, on the way as they came out of Egypt, had not been circumcised. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 For the children of Israel walked forty years in the wilderness, till all the people who were men of war, who came out of Egypt, were consumed, because they did not obey the voice of the LORD--to whom the LORD swore that He would not show them the land which the LORD had sworn to their fathers that He would give us, "a land flowing with milk and honey." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Joshua circumcised their sons whom He raised up in their place; for they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised on the way. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it was, when they had finished circumcising all the people, that they stayed in their places in the camp till they were healed. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD said to Joshua, "This day I have rolled away the reproach of Egypt from you." Therefore the name of the place is called Gilgal to this day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now the children of Israel camped in Gilgal, and kept the Passover on the fourteenth day of the month at twilight on the plains of Jericho. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And they ate of the produce of the land on the day after the Passover, unleavened bread and parched grain, on the very same day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the manna ceased on the day after they had eaten the produce of the land; and the children of Israel no longer had manna, but they ate the food of the land of Canaan that year. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it came to pass, when Joshua was by Jericho, that he lifted his eyes and looked, and behold, a Man stood opposite him with His sword drawn in His hand. And Joshua went to Him and said to Him, "Are You for us or for our adversaries?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So He said, "No, but as Commander of the army of the LORD I have now come." And Joshua fell on his face to the earth and worshiped, and said to Him, "What does my Lord say to His servant?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the Commander of the LORD's army said to Joshua, "Take your sandal off your foot, for the place where you stand is holy." And Joshua did so. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 6
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now Jericho was securely shut up because of the children of Israel; none went out, and none came in. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD said to Joshua: "See! I have given Jericho into your hand, its king, and the mighty men of valor. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 You shall march around the city, all you men of war; you shall go all around the city once. This you shall do six days. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And seven priests shall bear seven trumpets of rams' horns before the ark. But the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times, and the priests shall blow the trumpets. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
