\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 from Aroer which is on the bank of the River Arnon, and the town that is in the midst of the ravine, and all the plain of Medeba as far as Dibon; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, as far as the border of the children of Ammon; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Gilead, and the border of the Geshurites and Maachathites, all Mount Hermon, and all Bashan as far as Salcah; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and Edrei, who remained of the remnant of the giants; for Moses had defeated and cast out these. 
\f0\fs24 \

